To determine how long it will take to dry seven pairs of socks under the same weather conditions, we need to know the weather conditions and other factors that affect drying time such as temperature, humidity, and airflow. 

Assuming ideal drying conditions with no interruptions, typically, it takes about 20-40 minutes for a load of laundry to dry in a dryer or on a clothesline. To calculate the time needed to dry seven pairs of socks, we can estimate that each pair will take around 30 minutes to dry. Therefore, it would take approximately 7 x 30 = <<7*30=210>>210 minutes for Tom to dry seven pairs of socks under ideal conditions.
